### Remaining Concerns (deliberately not "fixed" — they're content calls, not cohesion breaks)

1. **Diagnosis pre-tells Cincinnati.** The Type 7 section already delivers the weed story, the "worked out perfect" line, and the marijuana joke, so Cincinnati re-tells beats the reader has heard. The draft's own second-pass note flags this as intentional layering (diagnosis = the reflex; Cincinnati = the case file). It reads fine, but it's the one spot where the through-line doubles back. Your call whether to thin the diagnosis version.

2. **"Can't Do Just One Thing" holds three sub-threads** under one roof — the breadth-vs-depth question, the "he actually cares about his reputation" GQ beat, and the 2025 stat low + comeback. They're loosely bound by "the Enthusiast at full stretch." Coherent, but the reputation beat leans more toward the Type 3 counter-read than toward breadth. Not a break; just the least unified section.

3. **Discipline → Super Bowl** rides on an implicit link ("went deep in one arena / never anywhere else" → the sideline being "anywhere else"). It works via the "happy-go-lucky myth" callback, so I left it rather than risk cluttering a strong opener. Flagging in case you want to make the depth-vs-combustion pivot explicit.

The piece was already cohesive, so I applied only the one transition that genuinely benefited and held off on forcing bridges where they'd have added noise.
